version_description: Chords for the "Oh Mercy" studio recording.
It is the alternate version from "Tell Tale Signs" Bootleg Series Volume 8.
Acoustic version from: "The Bootleg Series Vol. 08: Tell Tale Signs. " / https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lAzcPg5LR5k.
My version is true to the key of G as in Bob's version, and my chords are completed over the entire song.
Up two and a half steps from the original key, easy to play version.
"Bringing It All Back Home" version / Drop-D with capo 3rd fret / including intro, solo and outro / suggestions for voicings / thoroughly ear-transcribed.
Strumming pattern is optional, the original was not strummed but composed of simple riffs that aren't tabbed here.
Complete and well-aligned intermediate version with slash chords / all verses feature chords for convenient auto-scrolling.

There is one other tab/chord for this song and it's the same version and in fact every other site on the net has this same tab. The tab is incomplete it does not have the chords for all the verses. And I also corrected a few lyrics I picked up on , and the fill between each verse.
Complete and thoroughly ear-transcribed / intermediate version with split chords / short tab for the lick and suggestions for voicings of unusual chords.
Complete and well-aligned chords for the whole song / suggestions for playable voicings.

song_name: Oh Babe It Aint No Lie

version_description: There are no official lyrics to this song, so I've cobbled them together from others online and my own listening. The recording is in C#, which may mean it has been sped up, or that it was actually played in that key originally.
Well-aligned and complete chords for the live version from "At Budokan".
